WRITING.TEXT: Rest in peace
Rest in peace

My smile quickly faded into a very concerned look. "If finding a dollar corresponds to stabbing your toe...", I thought, while holding my lottery ticket,"then.. what does this mean?".
I quickly snapped out of my thoughts and began preparing for the worst. I hid the lottery ticket inside a locked drawer, I boarded up all of my windows, I locked all my doors. If something was going to kill me, it would have to get through all my defenses.
I then proceeded to sit on my couch and watch the news. Suddenly, I felt hungry. I got up and stretched as my stomach began to rumble. I slowly walked towards the kitchen, where I remembered having placed a bag of chips on the counter. I grab the bag and begin to walk back to the living room where my couch was located.
Suddenly a thought of dread came upon me. It almost felt like I was about to experience this ultimate payback for my lottery winning. My heart raced as I walked back into the living room. Then ,"BANG!". I had stubbed my toe.
